1 (a) Beginning with the 2025-2026 school year, each public school
2 serving students in grades six through twelve (6-12) shall provide
3 instruction on human growth and development.
4 (b) The human growth and development instruction required under
5 subsection (a) of this section shall include without limitation the
6 following:
7 (1) A high-definition ultrasound video, at least three (3)
8 minutes in duration, that shows the development of the brain, heart, sex
9 organs, and other vital organs in early fetal development; and
10 (2) A high-quality, computer-generated rendering or animation
11 that shows the process of fertilization and every stage of human development
12 inside the uterus, noting significant markers in cell growth and organ
13 development during each week of pregnancy until birth.
14 (c) The human growth and development instruction required under this
15 section shall be included in every class that discusses or provides
16 instruction concerning:
17 (1) Human biology;
18 (2) Contraception; or
19 (3) Sexually transmitted diseases or sexually transmitted
20 infections.
21 (d) As used in this section, "public school" means:
22 (1) A public school within a public school district; or
23 (2) An open-enrollment public charter school.
